From: Peter Zijlstra <peterz@infradead.org>
Date: Wed, 3 Apr 2024 09:50:12 +0200
Subject: sched/fair: Cleanup pick_task_fair()'s curr

With 4c456c9ad334 ("sched/fair: Remove unused 'curr' argument from
pick_next_entity()") curr is no longer being used, so no point in
clearing it.

Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 10 ++--------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
index b5dbd23662188a..d08150cca0ffbd 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -8433,15 +8433,9 @@ again:
 		return NULL;
 
 	do {
-		struct sched_entity *curr = cfs_rq->curr;
-
 		/* When we pick for a remote RQ, we'll not have done put_prev_entity() */
-		if (curr) {
-			if (curr->on_rq)
-				update_curr(cfs_rq);
-			else
-				curr = NULL;
-		}
+		if (cfs_rq->curr && cfs_rq->curr->on_rq)
+			update_curr(cfs_rq);
 
 		if (unlikely(check_cfs_rq_runtime(cfs_rq)))
 			goto again;
